Nigerian music star, David Adedeji Adeleke, has expressed optimism that his uncle, Ademola Adeleke of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, in the ongoing governorship election in Osun State, would win the race. Davido, in a series of tweets, urged voters to remain at the polling unit as counting continues despite heavy downpour. According to the singer, the stolen mandate of his uncle is being retrieved. He wrote, “It’s raining. We will dance in the rain! Don’t leave those collation centers ! Victory is close ! “Retrieving the Stolen mandate with full force IMOLE Adeleke is coming”! DAILY POST recalls that Davido’s uncle, Adeleke had earlier expressed satisfaction in the ongoing exercise after casting his vote.